start-details:

h2: Select Node

This node allows you to select specific columns from an input DataFrame. You can also rename columns and change their data types.

end-details:

start-examples:

h2: Select Node Example

Given the following dataset:

| ColumnA | ColumnB | ColumnC | ColumnD |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | A | 10.0 | 2023-01-01 |
| 2 | B | 20.5 | 2023-02-02 |
| 3 | C | 30.7 | 2023-03-03 |

If you configure the Select node to:

* Select columns `ColumnA` and `ColumnC`
* Rename `ColumnA` to `ID`
* Change the data type of `ColumnC` to integer

The output would be:

| ID | ColumnC |
|---|---|
| 1 | 10 |
| 2 | 20 |
| 3 | 30 |

end-examples:
